data.title: Ronneby – Travel guide at Wikivoyage
data.text:
Ronneby is a city in Blekinge.

Understand

[edit]

Ronneby is regarded as "The Garden of Sweden". Long known as a spa town, it features some historical streets in the town centre, a series of ornate guest houses along the river, and the spectacular parkland of the Brunnspark.

Get in

[edit]

Ronneby is about half an hour by train from Karlskrona on the line to Kristianstad and Malmö.

Get around

[edit]

Walking is easiest, with the town centre just north of the station and the riverside stretching south to the Brunnspark.

See

[edit]

Do

[edit]

Buy

[edit]

Eat

[edit]

There are a limited numbers of restaurants in the town centre and a few near the Brunnspark that are best for sunny lunches or summer weekends. There is a Willy's supermarket in town for picnic supplies.

Drink

[edit]

The Systemsbolaget is near the north end of the town centre and has limited hours. Several bar/restaurants are on the main square.
